#31949
{BO,R} Ruby Narthex {bo,r}~
  
  {BO,R}Tall pillars of ruby line the entrance to this section of the hatchery.
  Within the facets of the rubies along the walls, you begin to notice
  the rounded shapes of eggs, hundreds of them.  Where a few have
  already hatched, the ruby facets are crumbled and broken.  Signs show
  the slow healing of the rubies, preparing themselves for the next
  clutch of eggs.  Crimson whelps from the hatched eggs are creeling
  hungrily around you.{bo,r}
  
  
