{BO,CYAN}Languid Lake{bo,cyan}~
  
  
  {BO,CYAN}By this time the snow has become a steady driving fall, making it
  difficult to see more than a few feet ahead.  The wind buffets you and
  stings your eyes with thin shards of ice from the storm.  The sapphire
  spears have grown numerous, and you find you have lost sight of the
  dock entirely with their crowding.  The once sluggish waters of the
  lake have become slushy, congealing gradually into ice.
  is a blue dragon, whose eyes are no more than a pair of icy chips
  against its deep blue hide.  It raises its head and swivels it to
  inspect you as you alight upon its island.
